The paper proposes a face recognition algorithm for giant pandas using images captured by cameras in the wild. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques for feature extraction and matching, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the limitations of current population estimation approaches, which suggests that it could belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
